      Subclasses of Matrix in matrix.matrixImpl 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  MatrixFloat
      Provides implementation of a dense 2d matrix of float elements.
      class  MatrixSparse
      Provides implementation of a sparse 2d matrix.
      class  MatrixSparseHash
      Provides implementation of a sparse 2d matrix.
      class  MatrixSparseHashPar
      Implementation similar to that of MatrixSparseHash only that the MatrixSparseHashPar.fastMult(float) and MatrixSparseHashPar.fastMult(Matrix) operations are implemented in a multi-threaded manner
      class  MatrixSparseTrove
      Provides implementation of a sparse 2d matrix based on the Trove libraries.
      class  MatrixSparseTrovePar
      Implementation similar to that of MatrixSparseTrove only that the MatrixSparseTrovePar.fastMult(float) and MatrixSparseTrovePar.fastMult(Matrix) operations are implemented in a multi-threaded manner
      class  MatrixThreshold
      This matrix automatically changes it representation between MatrixSparseHash and MatrixFloat when its sparseness is lower or higher, respectively, than a threshold.
